Publication-ready volcano plots with enhanced colouring and labeling

Kevin Blighe

2018-07-16

Volcano plots represent a useful way to visualise the results of differential expression analyses. Here, we present a highly-configurable function that produces publication-ready volcano plots (Blighe 2018). EnhancedVolcano will attempt to fit as many transcript names in the plot window as possible, thus avoiding ‘clogging’ up the plot with labels that could not otherwise have been read.

Example volcano plots

Following data generated by tutorial of RNA-seq workflow: gene-level exploratory analysis and differential expression:

Load airway data:

source("https://bioconductor.org/biocLite.R")
biocLite("airway")
library(airway)

library(magrittr)

data("airway")
airway$dex %<>% relevel("untrt")

Conduct differential expression using DESeq2:

library("DESeq2")
dds <- DESeqDataSet(airway, design = ~cell + dex)
dds <- DESeq(dds, betaPrior = FALSE)

res1 <- results(dds, contrast = c("dex", "trt", "untrt"))
res1 <- lfcShrink(dds, contrast = c("dex", "trt", "untrt"), res = res1)

res2 <- results(dds, contrast = c("cell", "N061011", "N61311"))
res2 <- lfcShrink(dds, contrast = c("cell", "N061011", "N61311"), res = res2)

Install and load EnhancedVolcano:

biocLite("EnhancedVolcano")
library(EnhancedVolcano)

Example 1: plot the most basic volcano plot:

EnhancedVolcano(res1, lab = rownames(res1), x = "log2FoldChange", y = "pvalue")

Example 1: plot the most basic volcano plot

Example 2: modify cut-offs for log2FC and pvalue; add title; adjust point and label size:

EnhancedVolcano(res2, lab = rownames(res2), x = "log2FoldChange", y = "pvalue", 
    pCutoff = 1e-11, FCcutoff = 1.5, transcriptPointSize = 1.5, transcriptLabSize = 3, 
    title = "N061011 versus N61311")

Example 2: modify cut-offs for log2FC and pvalue; add title; adjust point and label size

Example 3: adjust colour and alpha for point shading:

EnhancedVolcano(res2, lab = rownames(res2), x = "log2FoldChange", y = "pvalue", 
    pCutoff = 1e-11, FCcutoff = 1.5, transcriptPointSize = 1.5, transcriptLabSize = 3, 
    title = "N061011 versus N61311", col = c("black", "black", "black", "red3"), 
    colAlpha = 1)

Example 3: adjust colour and alpha for point shading

Example 4: adjust axis limits:

EnhancedVolcano(res2, lab = rownames(res2), x = "log2FoldChange", y = "pvalue", 
    pCutoff = 1e-11, FCcutoff = 1.5, transcriptPointSize = 1.5, transcriptLabSize = 3, 
    title = "N061011 versus N61311", colAlpha = 1, xlim = c(-8, 8), ylim = c(0, 
        -log10(1e-31)))

Example 4: adjust axis limits

Example 5: adjust cut-off lines:

EnhancedVolcano(res2, lab = rownames(res2), x = "log2FoldChange", y = "pvalue", 
    pCutoff = 1e-11, FCcutoff = 1.5, transcriptPointSize = 1.5, transcriptLabSize = 3, 
    title = "N061011 versus N61311", colAlpha = 1, xlim = c(-8, 8), ylim = c(0, 
        -log10(1e-31)), cutoffLineType = "twodash", cutoffLineCol = "red3", 
    cutoffLineWidth = 1.5)

Example 5: adjust cut-off lines

Example 6: adjust legend position, size, and text:

EnhancedVolcano(res2, lab = rownames(res2), x = "log2FoldChange", y = "pvalue", 
    pCutoff = 1e-11, FCcutoff = 1.5, transcriptPointSize = 1.5, transcriptLabSize = 3, 
    colAlpha = 1, cutoffLineType = "twodash", cutoffLineCol = "red4", cutoffLineWidth = 1, 
    legend = c("NS", "Log (base 2) fold-change", "P value", "P value & Log (base 2) fold-change"), 
    legendPosition = "right", legendLabSize = 14, legendIconSize = 5)

Example 6: adjust legend position, size, and text

Example 7: plot adjusted p-values:

EnhancedVolcano(res2, lab = rownames(res2), x = "log2FoldChange", y = "padj", 
    xlab = bquote(~Log[2] ~ "fold change"), ylab = bquote(~-Log[10] ~ adjusted ~ 
        italic(P)), pCutoff = 1e-04, FCcutoff = 1, xlim = c(-6, 6), transcriptLabSize = 3, 
    colAlpha = 1, legend = c("NS", "Log2 FC", "Adjusted p-value", "Adjusted p-value & Log2 FC"), 
    legendPosition = "bottom", legendLabSize = 10, legendIconSize = 3)

Example 7: plot adjusted p-values

Example 8: fit more labels by adding connectors:

EnhancedVolcano(res2, lab = rownames(res2), x = "log2FoldChange", y = "padj", 
    xlab = bquote(~Log[2] ~ "fold change"), ylab = bquote(~-Log[10] ~ adjusted ~ 
        italic(P)), pCutoff = 1e-04, FCcutoff = 2, xlim = c(-6, 6), transcriptLabSize = 3, 
    colAlpha = 1, legend = c("NS", "Log2 FC", "Adjusted p-value", "Adjusted p-value & Log2 FC"), 
    legendPosition = "bottom", legendLabSize = 10, legendIconSize = 3, DrawConnectors = TRUE, 
    widthConnectors = 0.5, colConnectors = "black")

Example 8: fit more labels by adding connectors

Example 9: only label key transcripts:

EnhancedVolcano(res2, lab = rownames(res2), x = "log2FoldChange", y = "padj", 
    selectLab = c("ENSG00000106565", "ENSG00000187758"), xlab = bquote(~Log[2] ~ 
        "fold change"), ylab = bquote(~-Log[10] ~ adjusted ~ italic(P)), pCutoff = 1e-04, 
    FCcutoff = 2, xlim = c(-6, 6), transcriptLabSize = 5, colAlpha = 1, legend = c("NS", 
        "Log2 FC", "Adjusted p-value", "Adjusted p-value & Log2 FC"), legendPosition = "bottom", 
    legendLabSize = 10, legendIconSize = 3)

Example 9: only label key transcripts

Example 10: plot multiple volcanos on the same page:

p1 <- EnhancedVolcano(res1, lab = rownames(res1), x = "log2FoldChange", y = "pvalue", 
    pCutoff = 1e-23, FCcutoff = 2, transcriptLabSize = 2, colAlpha = 1, legendPosition = "bottom", 
    legendLabSize = 10, legendIconSize = 3)

p2 <- EnhancedVolcano(res2, lab = rownames(res2), x = "log2FoldChange", y = "padj", 
    selectLab = c("ENSG00000106565", "ENSG00000187758"), xlab = bquote(~Log[2] ~ 
        "fold change"), ylab = bquote(~-Log[10] ~ adjusted ~ italic(P)), pCutoff = 1e-04, 
    FCcutoff = 2, xlim = c(-6, 6), transcriptLabSize = 5, colAlpha = 1, legend = c("NS", 
        "Log2 FC", "Adjusted p-value", "Adjusted p-value & Log2 FC"), legendPosition = "bottom", 
    legendLabSize = 10, legendIconSize = 3)


library(gridExtra)
library(grid)
grid.arrange(p1, p2, ncol = 2, top = "EnhancedVolcano")
grid.rect(gp = gpar(fill = NA))

Example 10: plot multiple volcanos on the same page
